[{"sha":"a764161955c796704e9c886d7af14172b6396115","author":{"name":"Jacques Pienaar","email":"8b5f536c3e2f2b8ae266b27bc9085a584b5bd904@google.com"},"message":"Don't fold XLA TF ops

Folding these ops via dialect fallback results in invoking the XLA CPU compiler. The folding via eager execution would result in using the XLA on demand op execution, which is currently only really enabled for tests and even for tests we intend to migrate away from them. Disabling the folding here would mostly result in deferring the folding to XLA compilation time. If needed, we can add folding here again for these ops while avoiding using the on demand compilation workflow.

[{"sha":"02ca4e970c44e2ec6cbe7dab6ab90f7866aacb38","author":{"name":"Martin Atkins","email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk"},"message":"go.mod: replace github.com/dgrijalva/jwt-go with .../golang-jwt/jwt

CVE-2020-26160 is a high-severity advisory reported against this module.

The dgrijalva package is no longer maintained but our legacy etcv2 backend
depends on it indirectly, via go.etcd.io/etcd/client. The golang-jwt
package is the blessed successor of the original, and has a v3 line which
is compatible with the v3 line of dgrijalva, and so through this replace
we can get a fix for the advisory without other significant behavior
change.

We've preserved the etcdv2 backend as-is on a best-effort basis in order
to support anyone who is already using it, but recommend that users switch
to etcdv3 or to some other backend for ongoing use.

We also have future plans to make state storage be a matter for provider
plugins rather than built in to Terraform CLI, at which point this backend
will either become obsolete or be factored out into its own plugin, at
which point we can remove this "replace" directive and the associated
dependency altogether.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/02ca4e970c44e2ec6cbe7dab6ab90f7866aacb38"}]

This commit is part of NETBEANS-5673, which modernizes the look of NetBeans'
window system tabs on the Windows LAF, and makes the tabs look good on various
HiDPI resolutions. I decided to use the FlatLAF tab displayer implementations as
a starting point for the new look rather than the old Windows LAF
implementations, as FlatLAF already handles HiDPI scaling, and has convenient
configuration settings.

This commit does a "clean" copy of a few files from the o.n.swing.laf.flatlaf
module to the o.n.swing.tabcontrol module, only doing as much refactoring as
necessary to avoid dependencies on the actual external FlatLAF library and its
configuration files. Configuration constants are added to Windows8LFCustoms,

the configuration and tab displayer implementations to actually look like

This commit contains various improvements to the tab painting classes that were
copied to the Windows LAF from FlatLAF in the previous commit. These particular
changes may later be ported back to FlatLAF if desired. In this commit, we do
not yet change the actual styling of the tabs.

Details:
* Align and connect borders between tabs and the container panel below,
  including on fractional HiDPI scalings (e.g. 150%). Some visual artifacts
  still exist, e.g. on 125% scaling, but they are less common, and not very
  visible.
* Improve the behavior of DPIUnscaledBorder in more cases.
* Add new configuration options to the TabDisplayerUI classes, to prepare for
  the new tab style on Windows, but do not yet make use of them. This includes
  the ability to draw a border around the selected tab, the ability to set a
  separate hover color for unselected tabs, and support for a color gradient in
  the selected editor tab.
* In editor tabs, avoid showing a tab separator after the last tab.
* In editor tabs, properly handle clipped tabs.
* In view tabs, properly allocate space for the animated "busy" icon.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/apache/netbeans/commits/684368f42bc4399d71b2d7ca6c872e3907f017f0"},{"sha":"df0cada60669664507d0266314d7b76728d92308","author":{"name":"Eirik Bakke","email":"ddeb4d9fbbe24684d42173e2d1bd3773f25d1719@ultorg.com"},"message":"Replace the bitmap 'busy' icon with a manually drawn spinner that scales well on HiDPI/Retina screens.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/apache/netbeans/commits/df0cada60669664507d0266314d7b76728d92308"},{"sha":"ad7eea77d996624caf520aa32cfced8250848882","author":{"name":"Eirik Bakke","email":"ddeb4d9fbbe24684d42173e2d1bd3773f25d1719@ultorg.com"},"message":"Adjust some borders on the Windows LAF, and other smaller tweaks.

configuration is not evaluated, so they cannot be configured).
